Although unlinked COVID-19 cases have been detected in increasing numbers since early March, transmissibility (R
t) remains around the critical threshold of 1 (figure 2
). Increases in local cases could be attributed to the transmission of infections into the community, resulting from an increasing number of imported infections since early March. With a local effective reproduction number of 1, a gradual increase in the incidence of local infections would be expected.
